    Scope and Contents
Mrs. Miller, superintendent of Springfield's Washington Street Mission, recalls her father and family life; the establishment and history of the Mission; mission to Mexico; work with families in need; satisfactions and rewards; and the relocation of the Mission.4 tapes, 360 mins., 2 vols., 139 pp.
Interview by Margaret M. Klusmeyer, 1973
OPEN
